For the record my view is that people love a bandwagon and bashing Roblox for a scam is something to do for views or retweets.

But there is no smoke without fire, and if you put yourself in young devs shoes with no discovery or robux, I think you'd think it was exploitative too.

The devs that say it isn't a scam are those at the top but you're not thinking of all the devs at the bottom struggling to get even 10 visits

I don't think we have the right to tell young devs "it's not a scam your games just aren't good enough" when the problem is Roblox itself

Here's something controversial but I think a lot of young devs who have had zero traction on their games because of bad discovery (and no robux to advertise) DO think Roblox is a scam where they have zero chance of making money despite all their effort.
